definitions.definition: Pertaining to accident and not essence ; thus, inessential ; incidental ; secondary .

subdefinitions.definition: Nonessential to something's inherent nature (especially in Aristotelian thought).

definitions.definition: Adjusted by one or two semitones , in temporary departure from the key signature .
Happening by chance, or unexpectedly ; taking place not according to the usual course of things; by accident , unintentional .
Being a double point with two distinct tangent planes in 4-dimensional projective space.

main_definition: Pertaining to accident and not essence ; thus, inessential ; incidental ; secondary . [from 14th c.]
